    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** serving as the undisputed anchor of the lineup. With a robust 75.27 efficiency score, **Merrill** benefits from a high-upside matchup against Feltner, amplified by a favorable 14% park factor and a 15% boost from Feltner\u2019s elevated xERA. While speed is our primary currency, the ability of **Merrill** to exploit this specific pitching profile makes him our primary offensive engine. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Kyle Tucker**; despite their talent, the volatility of facing elite arms like Ryan and Webb necessitates careful management. **Luis Robert Jr.** is currently skating by on his elite sprint speed, which adds a 4% floor boost against the slower delivery of Ryan, helping offset a daunting 16% penalty for the opposing pitcher's skill.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involves the utility slot, where **Marcell Ozuna** barely held onto his spot with a 43.30 score, narrowly edging out **Josh Jung**. **Josh Jung** fell just short of our 40.0 \"Zebra\" floor at 39.89, with his matchup against Chandler hindered by a significant 19% SP skill penalty that suppressed his overall outlook. Our internal projections remain cautious regarding **Marcell Ozuna** due to his poor historical BvP against deGrom, but he remains in the lineup simply because he offers higher projected raw power than the available alternatives. We continue to monitor the status of **Jordan Westburg** on the IL, alongside our other high-upside bench assets like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Gunnar Henderson**, both of whom are sidelined by team off-days. Should **Drake Baldwin** struggle in the #2 hole, we will be forced to look toward our depth pieces, though today's priority remains maximizing every stolen base opportunity presented by **Nasim Nunez** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** against Ritchie.",
